deck: An Inhuman.
description:
History

Jack was a member of an Australian extremist group of human zealots. When Jack became an Inhuman, he became appalled in what he was turned into. He attacked the Royal Inhuman ambassador Crystal out of hatred, along with the help of his group. During the chaos, Jack's comrades noticed Jack's true nature and turned against him. Despite Jack's pleas explaining that he was still one of them, the group offered Jack a quick death. Jack and his former companions were defeated by Crystal and the rest of the Royal Inhuman Diplomatic Mission after which an Inhuman by the name of Ash Minnick, who was captured earlier by Jack and his group, was freed. Jack was imprisoned until later when Gorgon offered to train him to use his powers.

During his training, Jack took the opportunity he had to escape. He jumped into a portal that was used to produce training equipment from a place inside the Moon called the Storage. The Storage is an armory and the last visage of old Attilan, used by the Inhumans in case a situation gets dire and they need weaponry fast. Gorgon, Ash, and Naja used Lockjaw to follow and recapture Jack, however after a short confrontation Jack shot a hole into a glass window and escaped into the Blue Area of the Moon. He was eventually picked up by someone he had contacted previously while he was in the Storage having used a stolen communicator.
name: Jack

deck: Former dictator of Sin-Cong.
description:
This is the second known Commissar of Sin-Cong, the former was his father, Major Hoy, who was defeated by the Avengers. He placed his father's head in body of a rebuilt robot that his father had used to make believe was the Commissar but in reality he was the one operating it.

The Second Commissar ended up getting into a skirmish with the Inhumans which led to his imprisonment in Sin-Cong. His father had "woken" up and resumed command, but in reality he and the robotic body was being controlled by an Inhuman called the Living Dream.
name: Commissar of Sin-Cong

deck: The current dictator of Sin-Cong.
description:
Hoy or Major Hoy at the time was the secret dictator of Sin-Cong. Hoy used a giant robot to enact his terror plots and even pitted the machine against the Avengers which ultimately led to both his and the machines defeat. The machine itself was only ever refereed to as Commissar and was made to look like an actual person in order to keep the people of Sin-Cong in line due to fear of its power. When the Avengers ran Hoy off his son some time later took over Sin-Cong and placed his father's still semi alive head in the body of a rebuilt Commissar.

During his son's skirmish with Crystal's team of Inhumans a hostile Inhuman named Living Dream took over both the mind of Hoy and the robotic body he was installed in, "waking" the former dictator from his coma to be the rightful ruler of the "true" Sin-Cong.
name: Hoy

deck: "The Draftsman", a man able to see the future by painting vision
description:
History

After receiving special power after the exposure to radiation for a nuclear central breakdown in Russia, Gavriil Danilov, alongsite with many others, have been imprisoned into "La Cittadella degli Speciali" [The Citadel of Specials], a City Sized prison in Siberia, where the Soviet Government start to study them.

While in prison, he meet Andreji, another Special, and the two become friends.

With the crumble of the Sovient in Russia, the Specials rebel and take the City of Specials, transforming into their revolutionary base. Gavril, Andreij and some others don't accept the new leadership and try to escape, prefering to be free instead than imprisoned under some sort of "Revolutionary Special Leader"

Both Gavriil and Andreji [wich was escaping carring with him his two newborn] leave Russia, and the two depart in different way. Nothing is know of the life of Gavriil after the escape, but he and Andreji keep each others in contact while hiding from La Divisione.

However, Gavriil is later captured and forced by his former inmate to work for the organization, using his special powers to track enemies and others things for La Divisione. Among that, he was used to track the two child of Andreji, Michele Silenzi and an unknow girl.

After the events of the Movie, Gavriil is still imprisoned by La Divisione, and forced to work for them.

The special gift of Gavriil give him the ability to search and track a person or an object, with a slight degree of pre and post cognition, carving his vision into large immagine on walls and others surface. While quite accurate, years of using his special "vision" had leaved Gavriil mentally broken and instable.

NOTE:

The Character have been created by Gabriele Salvatores, Film Director, while Diego Cajelli is the writer of the comic.
name: Il Disegnatore

deck: Atletic teen, the loved one of Michele Silenzi [Il Ragazzo Invisibile]
description:
History

Young teenager girls, Stella Morrison is the new classmate of Michele Silenzi, "Il Ragazzo Invisibile".

Nothing is know of her family, exept that his father must often travel for work, and so Stella [who perhaps have at least one non-italian parents] have changed often school and city following her family.

A normal girl with great intellect and a talent in acrobatic and gymnastic at agonistic level, she befriend Michele, due being news and with no prejudice on the boy [usually bullied by classmate]. The young boy however, fall in love for her.

When Artiglio and the soldiers of La Divisione start to kidnap young talented boys and girls searching for the sons of Andreji, Stella will be captured and, later, used by Artiglio to lure in trap the young superhero. While in captivity, Stella show even greater ability in atletics and a good leadership, trying to escape from their prison and guide the others kidnaped boys, and she was also able to hold and use [not against people, however] a gun, inspite her young age.

Saved by Michele, she discover his secret identity, and fall in love with him, but in the end of the Movie, Andreji erease her memory, alongside that of all the others boys and people who have discovered the Andreji and Michele stories, leaving her only as a friend of the young hero.

NOTE:

The Character have been created by Gabriele Salvatores, Film Director, while Diego Cajelli is the writer of the comic. The major part of his history is showed in the Film "Il Ragazzo Invisibile", while in the comics she is only a minor character, since the comics is focused on the parents of Michele Silenzi and the history of La Divisione.

IN OTHER MEDIA:

Michele Silenzi is played by young italian actress Noa Zatta
name: Stella Morrison

deck: "Claw", is on of the Leader the La Divisione with the ability of control minds
description:
History

After receiving special powers after the exposure to radiation for a nuclear central breakdown in Russia, Piotr Abramov, alongsite with many others, have been imprisoned into "La Cittadella degli Speciali" [The Citadel of Specials], a City Sized prison in Siberia, where the Soviet Government, using the special department "La Divisione" start to study them.

While in prison, he meet both Andreji and Yelena, becoming a friend of both. Due to his powers, he was soon considerated one of the most dangerous of the Specials, and keeped under special security.

Piotr is able to take full controll of the mind of a person. His special abilities require he make a grip with his right and [only his right hand] on the victim, so his codename became "Artiglio", "Claw". Once he gets his claw on a person, he gain full controll of his brain even after leaving the grip: the victim may act normally but always under mental control of Artiglio, even at great distance. The link between Artiglio and a victim may be broken only hurting the Special, or if he chose another victim. However, as for any others Special, this power have a phisycal drawback, and the legs of Priot start to lose strenght, till Artiglio is forced to use a wheelchair.

With the crumble of the Sovient in Russia, the Specials rebels, and Artiglio, thanks to the aid of Andreji and many others such as Libellula and Elastica, take control of he City of Specials and proclaim himself new leader of the La Divisione. However, his first task become to pursuit who dosen't share his goal, such as Andreji, Yelena and Gavriil.

Years later, Artiglio reapear in Trieste, guiding a pack of soldier of La Divisione, and trying to find the two child of Andreji and Yelena, but having no real clue on their appearance, using mind-controlled people he start to kidnap teen that may have specials talents. One of them was Stella Morrison, a young girl with great atletique and intelligent skills, for which Michele Silenzi [the real son of Andreji and Yelena] had fallen in love.

During the final confrontation, Artiglio seems to die in the explosion of his submarine. However, after his dead, is showed that he was no longer the head of La Divisione, having lost the leadership years ago in favor of Yelena itself

NOTE:

The Character have been created by Gabriele Salvatores, Film Director, while Diego Cajelli is the writer of the comic.

IN OTHER MEDIA:

Artiglio is played by french actor Vernon Dobtcheff
name: Artiglio
